{[%evp 0,90,19,24,27,26,14,12,13,13,24,17,-36,21,27,20,19,23,26,-40,-47,-28,0,-9,-3,4,15,0,0,-1,6,1,-4,12,37,-23,7,0,9,12,27,33,23,7,54,-42,-33,-59,-185,-94,6,90,23,21,58,62,56,136,51,119,53,18,-1,1,-1,-2,-1,-1,59,-8,1,-81,1,-162,-203,-285,-249,-417,378,392,399,368,373,361,414,259,453,267,542,343,649,421,820]} 1. c4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 e6 5. b3 Nbd7 6. Bd3 b6 7. Nbd2 Bb7 8. Bb2 Be7 9. e4 dxe4 10. Nxe4 Nxe4 11. Bxe4 Nf6 12. Bc2 Bb4+ 13. Kf1 Be7 14. h4 c5 15. Qe2 cxd4 16. Nxd4 Qc7 17. Rd1 a6 18. Nf3 b5 19. Rh3 bxc4 20. bxc4 O-O 21. Ng5 Rfd8 22. Bd3 h6 23. Rg3 hxg5 24. hxg5 Ne4 25. Bxe4 Bxe4 26. Rxd8+ Qxd8 27. Qxe4 Qd1+ 28. Qe1 Qc2 29. Qc1 Qf5 30. Qc3 Qb1+ 31. Ke2 Bf8 32. Qb3 Bd6 33. Qc3 Bf8 34. Qb3 Rd8 35. Re3 Qh1 36. g4 Bc5 37. Rf3 Qb1 38. Rh3 $6 {[#]No era la mejor, pero dado que las blancas están perdidas, Pepe Cuenca plantea una astuta celada aprovechando los apuros de tiempo de su rival.} Bxf2 $4 ({Ganaba fácilmente} 38... Qe4+ 39. Kf1 Bxf2 $1 40. Qc3 Bd4 41. Qd3 Qf4+ 42. Qf3 Qxf3+ 43. Rxf3 Bxb2) 39. Rh8+ Kxh8 40. Bxg7+ Kxg7 41. Qxb1 Bd4 42. Qe4 a5 43. g6 fxg6 44. Qxe6 Bf6 45. c5 Rb8 1-0

